1) Yes, the field “dt_mode_of_transport_id“ could be used. You can also use relation, for example:

{noformat}            "dt_mode_of_transport": 
                "data": {
                    "type": "dtmodeoftransports",
                    "id": "IEC"
                }
            },{noformat}

These values are always the same, and we will keep both the attribute and the relationship in the API.

2) The values of “dt_freight_terms_jde_id“ and “dt_freight_handling_code_id“ are always the same in ORO and populated based on the order field with name “dt_freight_terms“ (has label “Freight Terms”).

I’d suggest using “dt_freight_terms_jde_id“ instead of “dt_freight_handling_code_id“ and eventually remove “dt_freight_handling_code_id“ from ORO API since there is no field like “Freight Handling Code“ in ORO.

