{quote}API notification will delay the project, we can use the query approach and then add API as enhancements.{quote}

It will not only delay the project but will not allow ORO to show real-time inventory availability value (because it should take into account reserved quantity in ORO, that should be cleared once Order reached JDE). So the only option is to make ORO read the data of this state from JDE DB using SQL. We just need to know which SQL to run for this use case.

20/Dec/23 1:19 PM;63247cbfa408c1e3a6592837;[~accountid:557058:ebfd60cd-ef4e-44c6-a5ff-1adfaf8f6b18] 

For example,

# The CSR could have selected some specific branch in the line, and do not want to change it →{color:#00b8d9} If the customer changes the branch needs to change for all branch fields. As some branch locations should not ship to certain customers depending on their location. I have discussed this scenario with you, there will be future fulfillment logic created in ORO post new year that will depend on this feature. The ship to customer’s branch should reset all branch fields as discussed. We are also adding a feature to do mass action selection{color}
# The CSR updated the Ship To or branch selected in the header, and submitted the order form → {color:#00b8d9}All branch fields should be populated with the ship to branch location for accurate fulfillment.{color}
# The application set the new branch from the header to all lines' Branch fields, and the selection made in step 1 was overridden → {color:#00b8d9}The user will need to make their selection again based on the new ship to customer’s branch location again. Fulfillment depends on the customer’s shipping options. This cannot be avoided. We discussed this on the touchbase 2 weeks ago.{color}

