* Use API of Order Error Case entity.
** When Order Error Case is new:
*** To add line items, send line item data in the request  {{POST /admin/api/entityordererrorcases}}
** When Order Error Case exists:
*** To add line items, send new line item data in the request  {{PATCH /admin/api/entityordererrorcases/{id}}}
*** To update line items, send updated line item data in the request  {{PATCH /admin/api/entityordererrorcases/{id}}}
*** To delete line items, send line item data excluding those that should be deleted in the request  {{PATCH /admin/api/entityordererrorcases/{id}}}. The line item that is excluded from the request will be deleted.
* Use separate API for Order Error Case Line Items entities:
** To add line items, send a request to  {{POST /admin/api/entityordererrorcaselineitems}}
** To update line items, send a request to  {{PATCH /admin/api/entityordererrorcaselineitems/{lineItemId}}}
** To delete line items, send a request to  {{DELETE /admin/api/entityordererrorcaselineitems/{lineItemId}}}

column166:
29/Nov/23 6:22 PM;557058:ebfd60cd-ef4e-44c6-a5ff-1adfaf8f6b18;[~accountid:5ef641d08624070abc725d7a], can you share an example of “Order Error Case” and “Credit Request Order Error” from PROD?

Oro has workflow running for these entities, and updating the status directly may not be the best option:

* The entity has a separate field “Status“
* The entity has a separate workflow that has “Step“
* Setting “Status“ directly will make the workflow out of sync with “Status”.

When Decisions needs to reject a “Credit Request Order Error“ it sends a PATCH request similar to this:

{noformat}PATCH {{base_url}}/admin/api/entitycreditrequestordererrors/18902
{
  "data": {
    "attributes": {
      "declinedReason": null,
      "isDeclined": true
    },
    "id": "18902",
    "type": "entitycreditrequestordererrors"
  }
}{noformat}

Oro’s workflow detects an update of the attribute “isDeclined“, and it runs a workflow transition that has the next actions:

* Move “Credit Request Order Error“ to Workflow Step “Rejected“
* Set the “Status” field of “Credit Request Order Error“ to “Rejected”
* Move related “Order Error Case“ to Workflow Step “Closed“
** Set the “Status” field of “Order Error Case“ to “Closed“

As a result, after this transition, the Workflow Status and Status fields of the entities are kept in sync.

I’d suggest using the next implementation:

# Decisions can use Oro API to find old “Order Error Case“
# Check if found “Order Error Case“ has a related “Credit Request Order Error“
## If it exists, send a PATCH request for this “Credit Request Order Error“ (similar to the example above). This action will Reject the “Credit Request Order Error“ and Close the “Order Error Case“
## If it is not found, send a PATCH request to “Order Error Case“ 
### Support for this request will need to be added on Oro’s side.
### The request will look like this:
{noformat}PATCH {{base_url}}/admin/api/entityordererrorcases/123
{
  "data": {
    "attributes": {
      "isItemFound": true
    },
    "id": "123",
    "type": "entityordererrorcases"
  }
}{noformat}
### The request is using the attribute “isItemFound“ because we already have a logic in Oro’s existing Workflow to Close the “Order Error Case” when this attribute is set to TRUE.
### Once the request is sent, the “Order Error Case“ will be moved to the “Closed“ Workflow Step and its Status will be updated to “Closed“.

